        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 3:32PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 332 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Foreman, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Foreman, Hooks, Richmond, Leary, Wallace, Arden, Red Bank, Almont
and Tom.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
